FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31007
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776764340
OL,3,CFinal designs revealed for Queen
OL,4,CElizabeth II memorial statue
OL,6,FThe figure they will see of Philip, in
OL,7,Fhis uniform, shows the duke standing
OL,8,Fas he often did with both arms behind
OL,9,Fhis back.
OL,11,FThe appearance of both statues will be
OL,12,Ffurther refined during the sculpting
OL,13,Fprocess.
OL,15,FThe Queen's former private secretary,
OL,16,FLord Janvrin, chairman of the Queen
OL,17,FElizabeth Memorial Committee, said:
OL,18,F"We thought it was very important that
OL,19,Fthe statue of the Queen, our head of
OL,20,Fstate, was on the ceremonial route in
OL,21,Fher own right.
OL,26,@zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1776764340
OL,3,CFinal designs revealed for Queen
OL,4,CElizabeth II memorial statue
OL,6,F"She will be depicted standing, on her
OL,7,Fown.
OL,9,F"But Prince Philip was such an
OL,10,Fimportant part ` they worked as a team
OL,11,F` of the realm that we've decided that
OL,12,Fhe should be a few paces behind the
OL,13,FQueen ` a position he was accustomed
OL,14,Fto."
OL,16,FHe added: "Prince Philip will be
OL,17,Flooking up because she is on a
OL,18,Fslightly higher pedestal."
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUvD@DO]xD@KOUzD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
